==在演化上的重要性==
生物灭绝事件时常加快地球生命的演化，因为灭绝事件时常使原本生态环境中占優勢的生物急剧衰落甚至绝灭，从而为新的生物的发展提供了更大的空间。在一个生态系统中，新的優勢种往往因此取代舊優勢物种，而不是由于[[性状|性状]]更优。<ref>{{cite book | last=Benton | first=M.J. | title=Vertebrate Palaeontology | publisher=Blackwell | year=2004 | chapter=6. Reptiles Of The Triassic | url=http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/book.asp?ref=0632056371 | isbn=0-04-566002-6 | access-date=2014-06-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081212023723/http://www.blackwellpublishing.com/book.asp?ref=0632056371 | archive-date=2008-12-12 | dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal| last=Van Valkenburgh | first= B.| year=1999 | title=Major patterns in the history of carnivorous mammals | journal=Annual Review of Earth and Planetary Sciences| volume= 27| pages= 463–493 | doi= 10.1146/annurev.earth.27.1.463|bibcode = 1999AREPS..27..463V }}</ref>如近年來研究認為，[[寒武紀大爆發|寒武紀大爆發]]跟[[埃迪卡拉紀末期滅絕事件|埃迪卡拉紀末期滅絕事件]]有關。

例如，[[哺乳形類|哺乳形類]]與[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]在[[恐龍|恐龍]]占優勢的[[中生代|中生代]]時期即已存在，但是無法與恐龍競爭大型[[脊椎動物|脊椎動物]]的[[生態區位|生態區位]]。[[白堊紀－第三紀滅絕事件|白堊紀－第三紀滅絕事件]]消滅了非[[鳥類|鳥類]][[恐龍|恐龍]]，使哺乳動物能夠進入大型脊椎動物的生態區位。恐龍亦是大滅絕的受益者，因為[[三疊紀-侏羅紀滅絕事件|三疊紀-侏羅紀滅絕事件]]消滅其最主要的競爭者[[伪鳄类|伪鳄类]]。

另一種觀點是{{link-en|提升假說| Escalation hypothesis}}，它預測在有較多物種競爭之生態區位的生物較不易在大滅絕中倖存。這是因為在大滅絕時的劇烈變化，將使原本一些能夠讓該物種維持一定穩定數量的[[性狀|性狀]]，在競爭物種數量急遽減少時反而變成負擔，進而加速其滅亡。

再者，許多在大滅絕中倖存的物種並未恢復原先的數量與多樣性，甚至有數量長期下降的趨勢（有時被稱作"{{link-en|越過死亡線的物種|Dead Clades Walking}}"<ref>{{cite journal| last=Jablonski| first= D.| year=2002| doi= 10.1073/pnas.102163299| title=Survival without recovery after mass extinctions| journal=PNAS| volume= 99| issue=12| pages= 8139–8144| pmid=12060760| pmc=123034|bibcode = 2002PNAS...99.8139J }}</ref>）。因此， 若以"哪些物種倖存或滅亡"的方式來分析某次大滅絕的話，往往會失於偏頗。

然而，[[達爾文|達爾文]]卻堅持，物種間的競爭，例如對食物或生存空間的競爭，在演化上相較於外在環境的變化來得重要。他在《[[物種源始|物種源始]]》一書中表示：
<blockquote>“物種是由緩慢起作用的原因產生和消滅的......有機變化的所有原因中最重要的是幾乎不依賴於改變的物理條件，即生物體與生物體的相互關係 - 一種生物體的改善需要改善或消滅他人。”<ref>Hallam, A., & Wignall, P. B. (2002). Mass Extinctions and Their Aftermath. New York: Oxford University Press Inc.</ref></blockquote>

==週期性==
部分學者認為，滅絕事件的發生具有週期性，大約是每2600萬至3000萬年之間<ref name=Raup1984>{{cite journal|title=Periodicity of extinctions in the geologic past|pages=801–805|issn=0027-8424|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America|volume=81|issue=3|date=1984-2|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6583680|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=D. M. Raup, J. J. Sepkoski|pmid=6583680|pmc=PMC344925|archive-date=2019-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016020133/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6583680|dead-url=no}}</ref>，或者大約每6200萬年就有一些波動變化。<ref name=Rohde2005>Different cycle lengths have been proposed; e.g. by {{cite journal|title=Cycles in fossil diversity|pages=208–210|issn=1476-4687|journal=Nature|volume=434|issue=7030|date=2005-03-10|doi=10.1038/nature03339|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15758998|accessdate=2019-02-13|author=Robert A. Rohde, Richard A. Muller|pmid=15758998|archive-date=2019-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610160901/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15758998|dead-url=no}}</ref>對於此種週期性有許多不同的解釋，例如太陽可能存在著一顆未知的[[伴星|伴星]]（[[涅墨西斯星|涅墨西斯星]]）<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://muller.lbl.gov/pages/lbl-nem.htm
|title=Nemesis
|author=R. A. Muller
|publisher=Muller.lbl.gov
|accessdate=2007-05-19
|archive-date=2019-01-15
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190115020524/http://muller.lbl.gov/pages/lbl-nem.htm
|dead-url=no
}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=13357
|title=Nemesis Reconsidered
|author=Adrian L. Melott and Richard K. Bambach
|publisher=[[Monthly_Notices_of_the_Royal_Astronomical_Society|Monthly Notices of the Royal Astronomical Society]]
|date=2010-07-02
|accessdate=2010-07-02
|archive-date=2017-04-02
|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170402205356/http://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=13357
|dead-url=no
}}</ref>，[[太陽系|太陽系]]在垂直[[銀河系|銀河系]][[銀盤|盤面]]方向的震盪運行，或者穿越銀河系的[[旋臂|旋臂]]。<ref name="Gillmana2008
">{{Cite journal| last1 = Gillman| first1 = Michael| last2 = Erenler| first2 = Hilary| title = The galactic cycle of extinction| journal = International Journal of Astrobiology| volume = 7| page = 17–26| year = 2008| doi = 10.1017/S1473550408004047| bibcode = 2008IJAsB...7...17G| url = http://oro.open.ac.uk/11603/1/S1473550408004047a.pdf| issn = 1475-3006| language = en| accessdate = 2018-04-02| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190601165347/http://oro.open.ac.uk/11603/1/S1473550408004047a.pdf| archive-date = 2019-06-01| dead-url = no}}</ref>

亦有學者認為，海中的滅絕事件並未符合週期性的假設，或者是該[[生態系|生態系]]逐漸達到了一個特定的臨界點，使大滅絕的發生變得不可避免。<ref name=Alroy2008>{{cite journal|pages=11536–11542|title=Dynamics of origination and extinction in the marine fossil record|volume=105|issue=Supplement 1|date=2008-08-12|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences|url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/doi/10.1073/pnas.0802597105|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=John Alroy|doi=10.1073/pnas.0802597105}}</ref>此外，週期性假說當中許多假設的相關性受到質疑。<ref>{{Cite journal| last1 = Bailer-Jones| first1 = C.A.L.| title = The evidence for and against astronomical impacts on climate change and mass extinctions: a review| url = https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-journal-of-astrobiology/article/evidence-for-and-against-astronomical-impacts-on-climate-change-and-mass-extinctions-a-review/734B16177C6E03B0D8BA6B2842F217AC| journal = International Journal of Astrobiology| volume = 8| issue = 3| pages = 213–219| date = 2009-07| doi = 10.1017/S147355040999005X| bibcode = 2009IJAsB...8..213B| arxiv = 0905.3919| issn = 1475-3006| language = en| accessdate = 2018-04-02| archive-date = 2019-01-25| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190125173139/https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/international-journal-of-astrobiology/article/evidence-for-and-against-astronomical-impacts-on-climate-change-and-mass-extinctions-a-review/734B16177C6E03B0D8BA6B2842F217AC| dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Testing the Link Between Terrestrial Climate Change and Galactic Spiral Arm Transit|journal=The Astrophysical Journal Letters|volume=705|issue=2|pages=L101|url=http://stacks.iop.org/1538-4357/705/i=2/a=L101|date=2009|doi=10.1088/0004-637x/705/2/l101|issn=1538-4357|language=en|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=Andrew C. Overholt, Adrian L. Melott, Martin Pohl}}</ref>但支持者則宣稱各種紀錄中皆有強烈證據顯示大滅絕的發生具有週期性<ref name="Melott & Thomas 2009">{{cite journal
 | author = Melott, A.L.
 |author2=Bambach, R.K.
 | year = 2011
 | title = A ubiquitous ~62-Myr periodic fluctuation superimposed on general trends in fossil biodiversity. I. Documentation
 | journal = Paleobiology
 | volume = 37
 | pages = 92–112
 | doi = 10.1666/09054.1
}}</ref>，且非生物性的地質化學資料亦有與其一致的週期性。<ref name="Melott et al. 2012">{{cite journal
 | author = Melott, A.L. et al.
 | year = 2012
 | title = A ~60 Myr periodicity is common to marine-87Sr/86Sr, fossil biodiversity, and large-scale sedimentation: what does the periodicity reflect?
